sentences: Calliope Tsoupaki (Greek: Καλλιόπη Τσουπάκη; born 27 May 1963) is a Greek pianist and composer.
She continued her studies with Louis Andriessen at the Royal Conservatory in The Hague, and graduated in 1992.
In 1993 she lived and worked in Budapest on a three-month residency from the Pepinières Foundation for young artists.
In 2007 she took a position teaching composition at Koninklijk Conservatorium.
Since 2018 Calliope Tsoupaki is the composer laureate of the Netherlands.
